Zelensky's office listed what weapons Ukraine wants to receive from the West

Mikhail Podolyak said that Western countries have problems with mathematics, because they do not understand the needs of the Ukrainian army and do not supply it adequately.

Continuing his answer, Podolyak listed the supply needs of the Armed Forces of Ukraine:

— 60 F-16 aircraft;
— 5-6 Patriot complexes;
— 200 thousand shells per month;
— Several hundred long-range missiles.

Upon completion of the transfer, he added that he did not understand the process of discussing the allocation of funds to Ukraine: “Here is the mathematics, it is very simple, I don’t understand what needs to be discussed here.”
